Subject: [PATCH] 340.108: build on Linux 7.0 & 7.1 (and 6.16+) + clang/LTO

Verified building against BOTH a 7.0 gcc kernel (7.0.13-zen) and 7.1 clang/ThinLTO
kernels (7.1.0-cachyos), and DKMS-installed on the real target (7.1-rc6 clang).
7.0 and 7.1 need identical deltas, so this single conditional patch covers both.

Fixes (cumulative on 0001-0019):
1. conftest.sh (kernel+uvm): add -fms-extensions. linux/fs.h now uses an anonymous
   tagged struct member; without the flag sizeof(struct filename) is wrong and the
   `static_assert(... % 64 == 0)` fails inside EVERY conftest that includes fs.h
   (surfaces as bogus vmap/acpi/pci_dma "conftest failed!").
2. os-interface.c: in_irq() -> in_hardirq() (in_irq removed).
3. screen_info: x86 boot global removed + not exported; new `screen_info` conftest
   gates NV_SCREEN_INFO_GLOBAL_PRESENT, users fall back to "no boot fb info".
4. dkms.conf (+uvm fragment): build with SYSSRC=/usr/lib/modules/$kernelver/build
   (NOT KERNEL_UNAME, which makes kbuild run syncconfig against the shared headers
   tree and break it) and auto-detect clang kernels (CONFIG_CC_IS_CLANG) to build
   with CC=clang LD=ld.lld LLVM=1 (else gcc dies on -mstack-alignment=8). SYSSRC
   also skips the gcc-only cc_version_check that fails on clang kernels.

--- a/kernel/conftest.sh	2026-06-26 01:32:02.309683983 +0300
+++ b/kernel/conftest.sh	2026-06-26 01:30:40.087357991 +0300
@@ -196,7 +196,7 @@
 }
 
 build_cflags() {
-    BASE_CFLAGS="-I${SCRIPTDIR} -std=gnu17 -O2 -Wno-implicit-function-declaration -Wno-incompatible-pointer-types -D__KERNEL__ \
+    BASE_CFLAGS="-I${SCRIPTDIR} -std=gnu17 -fms-extensions -O2 -Wno-implicit-function-declaration -Wno-incompatible-pointer-types -D__KERNEL__ \
 -DKBUILD_BASENAME=\"#conftest$$\" -DKBUILD_MODNAME=\"#conftest$$\" \
 -nostdinc -isystem $ISYSTEM"
 
@@ -572,6 +572,23 @@
             compile_check_conftest "$CODE" "NV_REMAP_PFN_RANGE_PRESENT" "" "functions"
         ;;
 
+        screen_info)
+            #
+            # Determine if the global 'screen_info' symbol is available.
+            # The x86 boot screen_info global was removed from generic kernel
+            # code in favour of the sysfb screen_info accessors (Linux ~6.15+),
+            # and is not exported to modules. Out-of-tree modules can therefore
+            # no longer reference it. When absent, the driver falls back to
+            # "no EFI/VESA boot framebuffer info".
+            #
+            CODE="
+            #include <linux/screen_info.h>
+            struct screen_info *conftest_screen_info(void) {
+                return &screen_info;
+            }"
+            compile_check_conftest "$CODE" "NV_SCREEN_INFO_GLOBAL_PRESENT" "" "generic"
+        ;;
+
         vmap)
             #
             # Determine if the vmap() function is present and how
